==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inequilateral
<hw>In*e`qui*lat"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having unequal sides; unsymmetrical; unequal-sided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the two ends unequal, as
in the clam, quahaug, and most lamellibranch shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inequilobate</ent>⟦br⟧
